295
00:21:45,346 --> 00:21:46,472
No.

296
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:50,142
What's extraordinary is
I've determined the exact height, weight

297
00:21:50,226 --> 00:21:51,769
and spinal curvature of this creature,

298
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:54,355
and my computer
can't find a single match for it

299
00:21:54,438 --> 00:21:56,982
anywhere in Earth's animal kingdom.

300
00:21:57,983 --> 00:22:02,571
This blackout was not a terrorist attack,
and that's no baby bigfoot.

301
00:22:02,655 --> 00:22:06,158
This guy is something else...

302
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:09,203
entirely.

303
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:12,039
Divert all search units
to the site of the footprint.

304
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:15,501
That's one small step for man,

305
00:22:15,584 --> 00:22:17,878
one giant leap for me.

306
00:22:29,139 --> 00:22:31,141
Okay, okay. Everything is fine.

307
00:22:31,225 --> 00:22:33,310
You played some baseball,
got a little upset,

308
00:22:33,394 --> 00:22:36,397
lightning shot out of your butt,
and now they're coming for you.

309
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:39,525
All right, ail right.
Earth isn't safe anymore.

310
00:22:39,608 --> 00:22:41,527
Time for plan B-- Mushroomville.

311
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:44,405
But I gotta take my stuff.
Okay, essential items only.

312
00:22:44,488 --> 00:22:46,824
Okay, toothbrush, toothpaste,
hair gel, night-light.

313
00:22:46,907 --> 00:22:48,951
Funny hat. This half-eaten cantaloupe.

314
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:50,911
And my scented candle.

315
00:22:50,995 --> 00:22:53,080
My entire comic book collection.
Beanbag chair.

316
